    <note>Chen(1) Xianbo [24820] He served in personnel administration. Shehe, the catagory for his method of entry, refers to the ritual of shedding commoner (buyi) clothing and taking official robes after passing the jinshi exam. CBD errs in identifying mode of entry with the facilitated military exam listing that precedes. I am treating 'shehe' as jinshi, though it may refer to some other process (perhaps by grace) of earning the degree, it certainly does not designate a miitary degree. Fujian TZ, 150.3b; Sanshan zhi, 32.23a. CBD, 3, 2647-8.</note>
